In the following example, the [compound](compound-ref) operator uses
[text](text-ref) operator to search for the term `Helsinki`
in the `plot` and `title` fields. The query for the `title`
field uses `score` with the `boost` option to multiply the
score results by 3, as specified in the `value` field.

```json
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "compound": {
        "should": [{
          "text": {
            "query": "Helsinki",
            "path": "plot"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": {
            "query": "Helsinki",
            "path": "title",
            "score": { "boost": { "value": 3 } }
          }
        }]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 5
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1,
      "plot": 1,
      "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" }
    }
  }
])
```

