In the following example, the [compound](compound-ref) operator
uses [text](text-ref) operator to search for the term
`Helsinki` in the `plot` and `title` fields. The query
against the `title` field uses `score` with the `boost`
option to multiply the score results by the numeric field
`imdb.rating` in `path`. If the numeric field isn't found in
the specified `path`, the operator multiplies the score of the
documents by `3`.

```json
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "compound": {
        "should": [{
          "text": {
            "query": "Helsinki",
            "path": "plot"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": {
            "query": "Helsinki",
            "path": "title",
            "score": {
              "boost": {
                "path": "imdb.rating",
                "undefined": 3
              }
            }
          }
        }]
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 5
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1,
      "plot": 1,
      "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" }
    }
  }
])
```

